The Dative of Purpose or Work contemplated is very frequent: the gerund or gerundive in this case may follow an adj., as dignam . . . suscipiendo . . . imperio, xiii 14, 3; or stand with a verb, as equivalent to a final clause, as testificando . . . vulgabat, xiii 11, 2; subruendo vallo inducit, xiii 39, 4, and many other instances, e.g. contegendis, xiii 13, 2; supplendis, xiii 7, 1 ; firmando, xiii 41, 3; visendis, xv 10, 4.
